Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.01,0:01:46.02,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The old guy received a letter from someone named Misao Nakamura,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.02,0:01:49.78,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}asking him to solve the strange mysteries of an inherited mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.65,0:01:54.42,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The mansion really was full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.62,0:02:00.13,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One handrail post by the front door\Nhad a tiger sculpture on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.13,0:02:03.80,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The other post had strange holes in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.80,0:02:06.47,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The house was filled with clocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.47,0:02:10.14,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}One clock had had something removed from it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.14,0:02:16.08,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}At exactly 11:00, all the digital clocks in the house rang.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.08,0:02:19.85,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The VCR's timer was set for exactly one minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.85,0:02:24.82,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}All the digital clocks had a crack in the same spot.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.82,0:02:29.12,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It all seems to have been set up to convey something.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.39,0:02:35.42,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What's more, someone seemed to be hiding in the attic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.43,0:02:41.77,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}In the desk was a file filled with newspaper clippings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.77,0:02:47.44,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}about the Goblins, a bandit gang that had disappeared 10 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.44,0:02:51.88,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Demon, the name of the Goblins' leader, was found on a golf bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.45,0:02:58.02,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Even stranger was the mirror affixed to the desk
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.02,0:03:01.11,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and the hole in the wall directly below the cuckoo clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.32,0:03:06.56,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And what came out of the cuckoo clock at 1:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.26,0:03:11.17,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...were ghastly goblin figures!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.47,0:03:16.06,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Where is the key to solving these mysteries?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.41,0:03:27.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon figures from the cuckoo clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.85,0:03:30.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Demons aren't animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:33.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What are such creepy things doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.02,0:03:35.96,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Those aren't just demons.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.96,0:03:37.79,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}They're definitely the goblin figures
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.79,0:03:41.76,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}the Bandits of the Wind used to leave behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.76,0:03:45.07,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But why three of them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.07,0:03:49.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's it! That's the weird thing I saw the other day!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.34,0:03:51.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.61,0:03:53.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,L-Look!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.34,0:03:57.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There are letters on each of their heads!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.35,0:04:06.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! What are these?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.02,0:04:09.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The far right demon has "R"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.73,0:04:13.59,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The middle one has "N"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.77,0:04:19.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the left demon has "L"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:27.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If the "L" and "R" mean "left" and "right,"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.74,0:04:30.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,what does the "N" in the middle mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.65,0:04:33.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,North?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.99,0:04:39.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.03,0:04:49.80,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When did those demons start crying out?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.80,0:04:52.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At exactly 1:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.03,0:04:56.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,1:10... That's another "110"...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.81,0:04:59.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.88,0:05:05.25,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,When I saw those earlier, it was at 10:50!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.02,0:05:12.32,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Not 1:10, but 10:50?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.32,0:05:14.29,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Does that mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.69,0:05:19.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Don't tell me those figures were...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.16,0:05:20.99,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Those{\i0} figures?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.37,0:05:23.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.35,0:05:25.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.84,0:05:30.54,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.54,0:05:34.87,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Now I see what's going on here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.85,0:05:40.82,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But I still can't figure out
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.82,0:05:45.62,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}what these strange signs and tricks Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} left behind mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.99,0:05:51.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The digital clocks and VCR all went off at 11:00...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.53,0:05:57.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The significant marks on all of the digital clocks' panels...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.23,0:06:01.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The cuckoo clock that suddenly went off at 1:10...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.30,0:06:05.74,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}And the three goblins that came out of the clock...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.74,0:06:11.48,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}...and the L, N, and R that were engraved on their foreheads...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.48,0:06:14.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}What is the key to answering all these mysteries?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.82,0:06:19.96,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.96,0:06:20.82,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's what?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.82,0:06:25.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you notice it while looking for animals around the house?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.23,0:06:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I {\i1}thought{\i0} something was missing!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.16,0:06:29.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.83,0:06:35.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't see any at all! They should be really easy to design, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.10,0:06:40.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stupid! There were two big lions on the front door!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.44,0:06:42.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? There were?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.75,0:06:47.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously, if he collected all these animals, he wouldn't forget lions.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.95,0:06:51.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The lion {\i1}is{\i0} the king of the animals!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.02,0:06:52.68,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}King?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.93,0:07:02.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.63,0:07:04.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What is it, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.50,0:07:08.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing! I just remembered something funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.24,0:07:12.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Weird kid.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.34,0:07:16.95,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If I'm right, it's truly a unique code!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.95,0:07:18.28,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But, wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.28,0:07:26.56,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If so, the letter O or the number 0 should've come out of the clock!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.56,0:07:31.66,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But L, N, and R came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.66,0:07:38.63,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could the cuckoo clock's code be separate from the digital clocks'?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.63,0:07:41.30,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}If so...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.30,0:07:45.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}1:10... 110...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.31,0:07:49.21,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The L, N, and R on their heads...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.21,0:07:51.71,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}A trio of goblins...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.71,0:07:56.05,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Trio... Three...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.05,0:08:00.12,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Triplets... Triplets?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.12,0:08:02.16,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The L, N, and R are triplets!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.16,0:08:04.53,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Wait a minute!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.53,0:08:06.52,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.53,0:08:09.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Could it be?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.51,0:08:21.88,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Ah! I've got it completely figured out!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.88,0:08:24.98,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.98,0:08:26.97,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.02,0:08:31.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Sheesh! Where did you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.19,0:08:34.29,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Where's your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.29,0:08:39.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In the study, still figuring out the code.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.09,0:08:41.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,At this rate, it's going to get dark soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.20,0:08:45.53,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Rushing won't help.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.07,0:08:48.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.47,0:08:54.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The answer might come\Nif we think hard into the night!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.87,0:09:08.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't figure it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.71,0:09:12.81,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The digital clocks all went off at 11:00 AM.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.81,0:09:19.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's a crack on all the digital panels after the digits "110"...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.79,0:09:25.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And the cuckoo clock rang at 1:10. Another "110."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.56,0:09:28.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They're all 110!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.63,0:09:31.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What does 110 mean?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.47,0:09:35.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it the emergency police number after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.17,0:09:40.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey. Maybe it's time we give up and go home?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:42.51,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}But it's strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:46.31,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It would've made more sense\Nto set the digital clocks to 1:10, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.31,0:09:49.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.35,0:09:51.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad! Earth to Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:56.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up! If you wanna go home, then go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.13,0:10:02.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get mad at {\i1}me{\i0}!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.97,0:10:11.14,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I guess it's late enough now.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.14,0:10:15.11,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,110... 110... 11...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.11,0:10:16.88,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! Stripes!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.88,0:10:21.45,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"11" refers to a striped pattern!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.45,0:10:26.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So if we check all the zebras in the house, we'll find something!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.92,0:10:31.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But wouldn't he have chosen 11:11 instead?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.63,0:10:35.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, tigers have stripes, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.83,0:10:40.03,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. There are striped cats, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.03,0:10:43.50,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Say. Which are stronger, zebras or tigers?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.50,0:10:45.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Tigers, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.41,0:10:48.38,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then tigers are the #1 animal?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.38,0:10:51.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Lions are probably #1, little boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.71,0:10:54.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! Lions are?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:56.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,No wonder they're called "king of all 60 beasts"!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.75,0:10:58.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,60?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.19,0:11:02.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You're dumb. They're "king of all 100 beasts."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.32,0:11:03.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,King of 100 beasts?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.32,0:11:03.79,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,hyaku jū no ō
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.79,0:11:06.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? King of 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.79,0:11:06.42,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,hyaku-jū no ō
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.96,0:11:11.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(150,0)\a6\bord0\shad0\fscx100\fs24}"King of all 100 Beasts"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.43,0:11:13.67,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it! I've figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.67,0:11:20.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This "1100" is a code referring to the king of all the beasts: the lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.74,0:11:24.78,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The mark between the zeroes
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.78,0:11:28.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,was trying to tell us to think of them as separate words!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.95,0:11:33.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Checking the lions will solve this mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.95,0:11:38.49,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But I don't see any lions...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.49,0:11:43.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} probably got rid of all unrelated lions in the house
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.30,0:11:46.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,to keep them from distracting us!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.90,0:11:50.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So that's why some things seemed broken or scraped away!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.90,0:11:53.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.37,0:11:57.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then are the lions in question the ones on the front door?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.48,0:12:02.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes! We should find something if we check them out!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.59,0:12:09.72,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing seems strange about them.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.72,0:12:11.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It would seem not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.76,0:12:16.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, how do you explain that cuckoo clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.30,0:12:21.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"King" in Japanese starts with the letter "O."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.27,0:12:27.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-True. "LNR" doesn't fit with the "king" thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.31,0:12:30.48,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it have meant something else?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.48,0:12:32.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That only appeared in the cuckoo clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.91,0:12:36.15,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't out of the question...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.15,0:12:41.12,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,...but then what? Is there yet another way to read 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.12,0:12:45.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's 1:10, so if you split the 1 and 10...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:49.36,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, "{\i1}i{\i0}," ten, "{\i1}to{\i0}"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.36,0:12:53.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,One, ten... One, "{\i1}to{\i0}"..."{\i1}Hi{\i0}," "{\i1}to{\i0}"...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:12:55.06,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Secluded Hot Spring (hitō)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.52,0:12:55.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Secluded hot spring?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.60,0:12:56.90,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Thread (ito)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.60,0:12:56.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Thread?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.44,0:12:58.77,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito (a last name)
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.44,0:12:58.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ito?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.01,0:13:01.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, Ito!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.01,0:13:05.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} know anyone named "Ito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.91,0:13:06.75,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.75,0:13:10.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then how about a Naito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} or a Saito{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.59,0:13:14.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so funny?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.65,0:13:22.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's neat! Changing the first letter makes completely different names!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.46,0:13:24.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's so neat about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.93,0:13:29.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Come to think of it, those goblins had letters on their heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.54,0:13:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,They all looked the same, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:37.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}The L, N, and R on their heads...\NAnd they looked the same?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.98,0:13:44.98,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Three similar words that start\Nwith L, N, and R, followed by 110?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.39,0:13:52.23,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.23,0:13:55.56,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.56,0:14:03.17,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The cuckoo clock code was saying to put L, N, and R before "ight"!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.17,0:14:07.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It was saying, "Light! Night! Right!"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.07,0:14:12.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Something will happen if we shine a light on the right lion at night!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.91,0:14:14.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Amazing, Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.91,0:14:18.61,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But you just shone light on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.92,0:14:21.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.59,0:14:28.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh? What could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.16,0:14:32.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See? Right behind the right lion!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.07,0:14:34.07,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.07,0:14:38.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not very obvious, but it looks like it opens up.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.38,0:14:45.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It does!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.41,0:14:50.18,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see! If you shine the light through here...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.18,0:14:51.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.55,0:14:56.92,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,T-This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.92,0:15:00.69,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Ran. Close the door and shine the light through here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.69,0:15:02.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Right!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.97,0:15:11.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The light is reflecting!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.74,0:15:15.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! There's a mirror in the post!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.44,0:15:18.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's just follow the light!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.99,0:15:32.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It goes inside the mansion through a hole in the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.43,0:15:35.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the hole in the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.46,0:15:38.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! To the study!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.43,0:15:42.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find anything?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.54,0:15:47.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep shining the light with the door closed!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.34,0:15:49.93,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? Still?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.75,0:15:56.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.36,0:16:09.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a bird this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.90,0:16:13.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.57,0:16:17.37,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The light from outside reflects off the mirror on the desk
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.37,0:16:20.47,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and shines on the cuckoo clock from below.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.47,0:16:23.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a photometer inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.14,0:16:23.10,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Photometer (light detector)
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.71,0:16:30.41,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be set up to only work at night,\Nso the sun won't set it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.72,0:16:34.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,There's something on the bird...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.76,0:16:37.42,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A wristwatch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.42,0:16:42.10,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! That must be a present our grandfather left for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.10,0:16:46.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It sure is fancy, though! It's covered with gems!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.23,0:16:50.77,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,If these are premium jewels, it could be worth billions of yen!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.77,0:16:55.28,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.28,0:16:58.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,it's probably a stolen item that Demon, the leader of the Goblins,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.55,0:17:01.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,secretly held on to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.58,0:17:05.22,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Demon, the leader of the Goblins?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.22,0:17:08.05,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The person who lived here: Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.05,0:17:11.06,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The figures that came out of the cuckoo clock
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.06,0:17:16.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,looked just like the goblin figures the bandit gang always left behind,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:20.00,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,and it looks like he received a golf bag with the alias "Demon" on it!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:26.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And I don't think either of them are the Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who sent the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.04,0:17:29.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,After all, the letter said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.04,0:17:32.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,"I haven't been here long and don't know the house well.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.08,0:17:35.08,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I figured I wouldn't discover anything on my own."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.08,0:17:40.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yet, they knew how to open the old door,\Nand they live here together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.02,0:17:46.83,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, he thought the cuckoo came out at 10:50 instead of 1:10.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.83,0:17:52.13,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,This is because he didn't see the clock directly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.13,0:17:59.04,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Instead, he looked through the hole and saw the clock in the mirror!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:04.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,In short, when Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} mentioned being watched by someone...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.71,0:18:07.55,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,that was referring to these two!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.55,0:18:11.02,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, I think Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is a woman.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:12.32,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.32,0:18:16.46,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here! Look at the stamp on this letter!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.46,0:18:19.86,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,See the lipstick on the underside?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.50,0:18:25.70,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh! She licked it when sticking it on here...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.70,0:18:30.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure you had this all figured out already!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.27,0:18:32.57,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, uhh, yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.57,0:18:34.73,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So, does that mean...?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.91,0:18:42.91,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Impressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.58,0:18:47.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the remnants of the Goblins.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.52,0:18:52.26,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,We came to get the last treasure our boss had held on to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.26,0:18:53.79,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Held on to?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.79,0:18:59.87,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah! When we disbanded, he gave us almost everything we stole,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.87,0:19:04.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,but he kept the most valuable items all for himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.60,0:19:08.34,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And those would be the jewels on this watch?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.34,0:19:12.21,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,He finally kicked the bucket,\Nso we decided to scour this house
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.21,0:19:17.52,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,he used to hole up in...\Nbut there was someone already here.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.52,0:19:22.19,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I assume it was the real Misao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nwho's locked in the attic now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.19,0:19:27.43,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah. When we tossed her up there,\Nshe just kept wailing on
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.43,0:19:32.27,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,about how some great detective\Nwould be here soon to get us.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.27,0:19:36.44,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,And then you showed up at the perfect time,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.44,0:19:42.31,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,so I pretended to be her to have you solve the code our boss left.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.31,0:19:45.58,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Now hand over the watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.58,0:19:49.14,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Hand it over quietly and I won't kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.19,0:19:54.09,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.42,0:19:57.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,B-Bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.33,0:20:06.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,What was that just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.20,0:20:08.90,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't move! Move and I snap her neck!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.90,0:20:10.20,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,You idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.20,0:20:12.23,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.12,0:20:26.85,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,A-A heel drop...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.65,0:20:30.89,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That scared me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.89,0:20:33.16,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It did?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.16,0:20:36.60,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Let's contact the police!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.42,0:22:10.19,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}After we contacted them,\Nthe local police rushed to the scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.19,0:22:14.49,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Still knocked out, the criminal duo\Nwas carried into ambulances,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.49,0:22:18.16,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}and Misao{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r} was rescued from the attic, safe and sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.16,0:22:23.90,Narration Off,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Just as I thought, she was the girl in the photo with Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Narration Off}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.24,0:22:27.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.51,0:22:29.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,So this was in the cuckoo clock?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.84,0:22:36.62,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} probably made the watch for you out of stolen jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.62,0:22:40.35,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody will know about it if you don't say anything...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.35,0:22:44.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,But stolen goods are stolen goods. I can't accept it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.39,0:22:47.39,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, my grandfather has already given me
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.39,0:22:49.63,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,something more valuable than jewels.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.63,0:22:51.30,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.30,0:22:55.74,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysteries scattered about this mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.74,0:23:00.71,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,For a mystery writer like me,\Nit's the greatest present!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.71,0:23:02.84,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.84,0:23:06.51,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Still, it's a waste...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.51,0:23:08.01,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.01,0:23:13.65,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Who knows, maybe it was actually meant for whoever found it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.65,0:23:15.66,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Then it's for me?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.66,0:23:17.76,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.76,0:23:21.59,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}I don't think so, old guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.59,0:23:28.40,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}That was most definitely a watch Monjiro{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r} made for Misao{\rHonorifics - Thoughts}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.40,0:23:31.47,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}Look closely at the watch face.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.47,0:23:36.57,Thoughts,,0000,0000,0000,,{\be10}It's stopped at 3:30. 330 can be read as "Misao."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.71,0:23:51.54,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,Nakai{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.15,0:23:59.95,Dialogue,,0000,0000,0000,,That's...!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.94,0:24:13.95,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Next Conan:
